The `last_response_()` function in R/last.R currently checks content type with:
r
if (!identical(resp_content_type(resp), "application/")) {
  cli::cli_abort("Last response doesn't have a JSON body.")
}


The package has a `check_content_type()` function that supports both exact type matching and suffix matching via `valid_types` and `valid_suffix` parameters. This function is used by `resp_body_()` which is why it works correctly.
